Perfect competition is rare

Perfect competition in the Long Run

  • Long Run - After firms have entered the market to drive profits down.
  • Short Run - Hold the number of firms fixed.

Review of Acronyms:

  • ATC - Average Total Cost \(\frac{TC}{Q}\)
  • AVC - Average Variable Cost \(\frac{VC}{Q}\)
  • MC - Marginal Cost (cost of one additional unit)
  • MR - Marginal Revenue (revenue from one additional unit)

Short run profit (P > ATC)

Source: Krugman and Wells.

Short run loss (P < ATC)

Source: Krugman and Wells.

Short Run Supply

Source: Krugman and Wells.

Short Run Equilibrium

Source: Krugman and Wells.

Long Run Equilibrium

Source: Krugman and Wells.
